<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-13-0626 </DOCNO><TEXT>This patent describes a method for providing a magnetic resonance imageof a region in a volume in the presence of a constant magnetic fieldthe steps of; exciting the region with a radio frequency burst; applyingmagnetic gradient waveforms to two orthogonal axes normal to the constantmagnetic field where the magnitudes of the two gradients are substantiallyconstant and the integral of the gradient waveforms, representing thespatial frequencies of the image, form an array of loops of increasingdistance from the origin; applying magnetic gradient waveforms whichcause the integral of the gradient waveforms to return to the originalong substantially the same array of loops; receiving magnetic resonantsignals while the gradient waveforms are applied; and processing themagnetic resonant signals to produce an image of the region.</TEXT></DOC>